==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Samian
<hw>Sa"mi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Samius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the island of
Samos.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fill high the cup with <qex>Samian</qex> wine.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Samian earth</b></col>, <cd>a species of clay from Samos,
formerly used in medicine as an astringent.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Samian
<hw>Sa"mi*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A native or inhabitant of
Samos.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samiel</ent>⟦br⟧
